          "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-17 14:35:55.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-5053 ptlrpc: fix for ptlrpcd soft lockup",
        "message": "LU-5053 ptlrpc: fix for ptlrpcd soft lockup\n\nThis patch changed a few things:\n\n- ptlrpcd can loop for long time without releasing CPU if upper\n  layer are consecutively adding new requests to ptlrpcd because\n  ptlrpcd_check() may always return true, this patch added\n  cond_resched() to ptlrpcd_check() and allow ptlrpcd yield cpu\n  when necessary\n\n- ptlrpcd_check() always scan all requests on ptlrpc_request_set\n  and try to finish completed requests, this is low efficience,\n  this patch improved this by moving completed requests at the\n  head of list in ptlrpc_check_set.\n\n  With this change, ptlrpcd_check doesn't need to scan the request\n  list for twice all the time.\n\n- l_wait_event() always checks condition for a two times before\n  sleeping and one more time after waking up, which means it will\n  call ptlrpcd_check() for three times in each loop.\n\n  This is very expensive because ptlrpcd_check will scan all requests\n  for 1-2 times.\n\n  This patch added \"wakeup version\" to ptlrpc_request_set, this\n  version number increases whenever reqset is scheduled for any\n  reason.\n\n  ptlrpcd will check this version number, if it's different with the\n  version that ptlrpcd has already checked, then ptlrpcd needs to\n  save the new version number and call into ptlrpc_check_set(),\n  otherwise ptlrpcd can skip scan.\n\n  With this change, ptlrpcd_check() could be much cheaper if it's\n  called for more than once in the same loop.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang.zhen@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I7880049cbaf7b8c0f7277346922b7a609d3af63f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
